1. What Data We Collect
We temporarily collect the following information during the upload process:
a. Image Upload Data
•	Image file uploaded by the user
•	Title of the file
•	Description / caption
•	Categories
•	License information
This data is required for uploading the image to Wikimedia Commons, where it becomes public.
2. What Data We Do NOT Collect
•	We do not store Wikimedia usernames or passwords.
•	We do not store uploaded files after the upload process is complete.
•	We do not collect personal information such as location, contact details, or device IDs.
•	We do not use cookies or tracking technologies unless added explicitly by the user.

3. How We Use the Collected Data
Collected data is used strictly for:
•	Processing uploads to Wikimedia Commons
•	Communicating with the MediaWiki API
•	Debugging errors
•	Improving functionality
We do not use data for marketing, analytics, or profiling.

4. Data Sharing
We only share your upload data with:
•	Wikimedia Commons (MediaWiki API) — to complete your upload.
No data is sold, rented, or shared with third-party entities.

5. Data Storage
•	Upload files are stored temporarily during the upload process.
•	Once the upload is completed, files are deleted automatically from the server.
•	No long-term storage of personal or file data occurs.

6. User Control
You may:
•	Stop using the application anytime
•	Choose which images to upload
•	Edit or delete uploaded images directly on Wikimedia Commons

7. Contact
For any questions about this policy, contact: [https://github.com/Wiki-For-All-Technical]
